    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 10, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-10",
    "tags": ["OpenAI IPO", "tech layoffs", "Tesla Optimus", "humanoid robots", "AMI Labs", "Yann LeCun"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 10, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 📉 OpenAI Makes $25B a Year, Loses More, and Is Definitely Going Public\n\nSam Altman wants a $1 trillion IPO by Q4 2026. His CFO would prefer everyone calm down first.\n\n- **The split:** CFO Sarah Friar told colleagues OpenAI isn't ready for a 2026 listing — the company projects $14B in losses this year and will burn \"hundreds of billions\" before hitting positive cash flow. Altman is briefing Wall Street banks on a ~$1T valuation anyway.\n- **The math:** $25B in annualized revenue. $2B a month in. More than that going out. A $110B private funding round — the largest in history — bought another year of runway.\n\n*\"Investing in the future\" is one way to describe losing $14 billion a year. Investors are apparently fine with this.*\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2026-04-08/openai-s-ipo-value-is-threatened-by-its-sam-altman-s-lack-of-focus) | [WinBuzzer](https://winbuzzer.com/2026/04/06/openai-ceo-cfo-split-ipo-timing-14b-loss-forecast-xcxwbn/)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 80,000 Tech Jobs Gone in Q1 2026 — Half of Them \"Because of AI\"\n\nNearly 80,000 tech workers were laid off in the first quarter of 2026. About half were explicitly blamed on AI. Whether that's accurate is a separate question.\n\n- **The numbers:** 78,557 layoffs in Q1 2026, 47.9% attributed to AI and automation. Block cut its workforce from 10,000 to under 6,000 in a single March announcement. Oracle followed with up to 30,000 positions in April.\n- **The counterargument:** Multiple experts call this \"AI-washing\" — using AI as a polished excuse for cost-cutting that would have happened anyway. Cognizant's Chief AI Officer says real displacement is still \"more than a year out.\" *(Cool. Great.)*\n\n*The AI revolution is creating enormous value. Mostly for the people who don't have to explain it to HR.*\n\n**Sources:** [Tom's Hardware](https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/tech-industry-lays-off-nearly-80-000-employees-in-the-first-quarter-of-2026-almost-50-percent-of-affected-positions-cut-due-to-ai) | [TechRadar](https://www.techradar.com/pro/nearly-80-000-tech-workers-have-already-lost-their-jobs-in-2026-and-ai-impact-means-more-could-be-to-come)\n\n---\n\n## 🦾 Tesla's Factories Are Run by Tesla Robots. The Robots Are Building More Robots.\n\nTesla has deployed over 1,000 Optimus units inside its Gigafactories and is targeting tens of thousands by year-end. Next milestone: robots assembling robots on a dedicated line.\n\n- **The deployment:** Optimus V3 handles autonomous parts processing at Gigafactory Texas and Fremont, running 24/7. Tesla's 2026 roadmap includes \"robot-built-robot lines\" — a phrase that nobody seems alarmed by.\n- **The competition:** Figure AI's Figure 03 is running continuous unsupervised operations in car factories using its Helix 02 system. Physical AI has officially moved from demo reels to factory floors.\n\n*The robots are assembling the robots. Nobody could have predicted this except everyone watching for three years.*\n\n**Sources:** [Humanoid Robotics Technology](https://humanoidroboticstechnology.com/industry-news/tesla-unveils-ambitious-optimus-humanoid-roadmap/) | [VFuture Media](https://vfuturemedia.com/future-tech/humanoid-robots-enter-the-workforce-figure-boston-dynamics-and-tesla-optimus-2026/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Yann LeCun Raised $1 Billion at Seed Stage. Europe Is Watching.\n\nAdvanced Machine Intelligence Labs just closed a $1.03B seed round — the largest in European history.\n\n- **The mission:** AMI Labs is building on LeCun's world model research — AI that understands physics and causality without the trillion-parameter brute force of LLMs. The stated goal is \"genuinely intelligent machines,\" not just very good autocomplete.\n- **The signal:** A $1.03B seed is larger than most US Series B rounds. European deep tech is beginning to attract capital at Silicon Valley scale, and LeCun's departure energy from Meta generated... enthusiasm.\n\n*Raising $1 billion at seed stage to build what LLMs can't do. Checks out.*\n\n**Sources:** [Crescendo AI](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-ai-news-and-updates) | [Radical Data Science](https://radicaldatascience.wordpress.com/2026/04/09/ai-news-briefs-bulletin-board-for-april-2026/)"
  }
]
